      "pipeline": "Approximately 4,700 undergraduates. Creighton is nationally recognized for pre-health and health sciences programs feeding directly into its own School of Medicine, School of Dentistry, School of Pharmacy and Health Professions, and College of Nursing. Major regional employers include CHI Health, Nebraska Medicine, and the concentrated Omaha healthcare and insurance corridor, alongside strong law and business placement regionally.",
